[{"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Oberfinanzdirektion Hannover S-2149 - 33 - StH 252 / S-2149 - 34 - StO 223S-2149 -EStK (LuF) \u00a7 13a EStG No. 11EStG: 13aEStG: 13a / 1 / 2EStG: 13a / 1 / 3EStG: 13a / 2EStG: 13a / 4EStG: 13a / 5EStG: 13a / 6 / 2EStG: 13a / 8EStG: 13a / 3 / 2AO: 162 Profits based on average rates according to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "When determining the profit from agriculture and forestry in accordance with Section 13a EStG, please note the following: I Farmers entitled to determine profits in accordance with Section 13a EStG In addition to Section 127 (3) to (10) EStR 1990 / R 127 (2) to (6) EStR 1993 I refer to the following: 1 initial value (Section 13a Paragraph 1 No. 2 EStG) (cf. Section 130 a Paragraph 2 EStR 1990 / R 130 a Paragraph 2 and 3 EStR 1993) .The Include areas that have been closed due to public funding programs (see Section 124 a Paragraph 3 Sentences 2 and 3 EStR 1990 / R 124 a Paragraph 3 EStR 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Surcharges according to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "In contrast to the determination of the economic value according to \u00a7 41 BewG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "\u00a7 141 Paragraph 1 No. 3 AO only to be taken into account if they are included in the relevant unit value (\u00a7 13a Paragraph 4 No. 1 Sentence 3 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "No separate market value is determined for publicly owned or exposed dykes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Since these areas are to be taken into account in the initial value in the case of leasing according to \u00a7 13a Paragraph 4 EStG, the full hectare value of the leaseholder's own areas would have to be applied"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "However, since the natural productivity and the economic yield conditions are lower than with normal agricultural land, dyke areas of 50% can be leased"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "the mean hectare value of the respective municipality or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Peasantry to be assumed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "If the valuation agency issues a \"negative value update\", the non-updated unit value continues to be decisive for determining the initial value"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Only for the area additions and disposals to be taken into account according to \u00a7 13a Paragraph 4 No. 1 Clause 6 EStG, the value shares attributable to these area changes can be taken from the \"negative value extrapolation\", insofar as the \"negative value extrapolation\" includes the area changes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "If a farmer and forester leases all of his land used for agriculture and forestry without this leasing leading to the abandonment of the business, an initial value in accordance with Section 13a (4) of the Income Tax Act (EStG) is not to be used even if the comparative, individual income or Hectare values \u200b\u200baround the value shares attributable to the leased area arithmetically an amount attributable to the farmer and forester because the farmer and forester no longer uses areas after the lease for which a value has to be taken into account according to \u00a7 13a para 4 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "The remaining amount is usually the portion of the value allocated to the courtyard and building areas"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "2 Animal population limit (\u00a7 13a Paragraph 1 No. 3 EStG) (cf. Section 127 Paragraph 7 EStR 1990) Exclusion from the personal scope of \u00a7 13a EStG due to the exceeding of the animal population limit of \u00a7 13a Paragraph 1 No. 3 EStG presupposes that increased animal husbandry was already being operated sustainably at the beginning of the financial year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "The principles of sustainability in the delimitation of agriculture and forestry / commercial operations are to be applied accordingly (Section 127 Paragraph 7 i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "V with section 124 a paragraph 4 and section 135 paragraph 4 sentences 3 to 8 EStR 1990 / R 124 a paragraph 2 and R 135 paragraph 2 sentences 3 to 8 EStR 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "When determining the livestock limit, third-party animals kept on the farm must also be taken into account. BFH judgment of 23 September 1988 - BStBl 1989 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "111)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "The maximum number of livestock converted into VE according to Section 13a Paragraph 1 No. 3 EStG and Section 13 Paragraph 1 No. 1 EStG can be found in Appendix 1"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "II notifications according to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Section 13a (1) sentence 2 EStG (see section 127 (8) EStR 1990) If the operational conditions have changed with effects on the level of the unit value in such a way that the prerequisites for a profit determination according to Section 13a EStG are no longer met, a notification i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "of Section 13a, Paragraph 1, Sentence 2 of the Income Tax Act will only be effective for the following financial year if the standard valuation notification taking into account the change is also available at the beginning of this financial year and which is authoritative according to Section 13a, Paragraph 4, No. 1 of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "It must therefore be ensured that the standard value notification taking into account the changes is issued in good time"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "A message according to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Section 13a (1) sentence 2 of the Income Tax Act requires the establishment of a new agricultural and forestry business (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "business transfer free of charge, establishment of a GbR, business lease) not (BFH judgment of 29 August 1985 - BFH / NV 1986 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "158)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Insofar as the start-up cannot be traced back to the takeover of a business that is subject to bookkeeping and thus the obligation to keep books exists (Section 141 (3) AO), the examination must be carried out to determine whether a profit determination is permissible in accordance with Section 13a of the Income Tax Act for the company newly established by the taxpayer to use the characteristics of the definitive unit value available at the time of the start-up"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "The type of profit determination of the previous business is - except in the cases of the transfer of the accounting obligation - irrelevant (BFH judgment of 26 June 1986 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "741)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Is a message i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 13a EStG has become final, but if the prerequisites for the determination of profits according to \u00a7 13a EStG are present at the beginning of the financial year following the notification, the legal effects are according to Section 127 (8) sentence 6 EStR 1990 / R 127 (2) sentence 1 EStR 1993 the final notification to eliminate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "If a farmer and forester asserts that he has set up an accounting or income surplus calculation in reliance on the notification issued in accordance with Section 13a (1) sentence 2 EStG and wants to base the taxation on the operating result, the farmer and forester's request can be be followed even if the application deadline pursuant to Section 13a (2) EStG is exceeded, if it was not aware that the prerequisites for determining the profit pursuant to Section 13a EStG had been met again by the beginning of the financial year due to changes in the operational situation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "In these cases, however, the farmer and forester is to be informed that the profit from agriculture and forestry for the next financial year according to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "\u00a7 13a EStG is to be determined if he does not submit an application according to \u00a7 13a Paragraph 2 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "The notification according to \u00a7 13a Paragraph 1 Clause 2 EStG should be announced one month before the start of the financial year to which it relates (Section 127 Paragraph 8 EStR 1990)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "The monthly deadline is intended to enable the farmer and forest manager to take the necessary precautions to set up a profit calculation before the start of the financial year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "However, it is not a preclusive period, so that a shortfall of a few days does not prevent the administrative act from becoming legally effective (BFH judgment of 23 June 1983 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "768)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "In this respect, nothing else applies than for a notification according to \u00a7 141 Paragraph 2 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Due to the notification of the notification - especially to companies - by delivery, I refer to the regulation in the AO card index \u00a7 122 AO card 2"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "If a farmer and forester, who determines the profit according to \u00a7 13a EStG, leases the business as a whole without the leasing leading to the cessation of the business, the profit is to be paid until a notification is issued i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 13a Paragraph 1 Sentence 2 EStG taking into account the special features resulting from the business lease (see IV No. 8 below) according to \u00a7 13a EStG (Paragraph 127 Paragraph 9 EStR 1990 / R 127 Paragraph 5 Sentence 2 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "EStR 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "With regard to this, in cases of business leasing, it must be ensured that the notification is made promptly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "III application according to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Section 13a (2) EStG (see Section 127 (4) EStR 1990 / R 127 (3) 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "234), which cannot be extended"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "The application for a different determination of profits can be withdrawn within the application period (Section 13a (2) sentence 3 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "An application according to Section 13a (2) EStG can - in addition to ticking the application in Annex L - also by attaching the profit determination made for the selected financial year to the tax return and entering the determined (gff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "pro rata) profit of the financial year in the fields provided for this in the tax return (Annex L or cover sheet) (see BFH rulings of January 28, 1988 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "530 and 532 and from 4 June 1992 - BStBl 1993 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "125)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "The submitted profit determination must be based on the actual keeping of books or recording of operating income and operating expenses (BFH judgment of 18 March 1993 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "549)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "If a farmer and forest manager, who falls under the personal scope of \u00a7 13a EStG, has determined the profit of a financial year by comparing the inventory or by comparing the operating income and operating expenses, but not an effective application according to \u00a7 13a para 2 sentence 2 EStG until the submission of the Tax return for the assessment period in which this fiscal year begins, but only for the assessment period in which the fiscal year ends, the actually determined profit is to be recorded proportionally in this assessment period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "For the previous assessment period, the pro-rata recording of the profit determined in accordance with Section 13a EStG remains"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "The binding effect of Section 13a, Paragraph 2, Sentence 1 of the Income Tax Act continues to exist for three additional financial years in accordance with the statutory regulation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "When changing the type of profit calculation, section 19 EStR 1990 / R 17 EStR 1993 must be observed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "IV Determination of profit 1 Basic amount (\u00a7 13a Paragraph 4 EStG) (see Section 130 a Paragraph 2 EStR 1990 / R 130 a Paragraph 1 and 2 EStR 1993) 2 Value of the work performed (Section 13a Paragraph 5 EStG) (see Section 130 a Paragraph 3 to 5 EStR 1990 / R 130 a Paragraph 3 to 5 EStR 1993) When determining the basic amount, it is assumed that the agricultural and forestry operations are managed exclusively with paid workers (Section 36 Paragraph 2 BewG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "The value of the work performed by the business owner and his unpaid relatives (Section 15 AO) must therefore be added to the basic amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "The addition can only be made for the number of workers (VAK) appropriate for the type and size of the company (Section 13a (5) No. 5 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "I would like to point out the following: a) When determining the value of the work for the physical work of the owner and the relatives who are not employed, only the work that is attributable to the areas included in the initial value according to Section 13a (4) of the Income Tax Act (Sect 130 a para 3 sentence 5 EStR 1990 / R 130 a para 5 EStR 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "b) Are relatives i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 15 AO due to an employment relationship that is to be recognized for tax purposes (Section 23 EStR 1990 / R 19 EStR 1993), like external paid workers, they are not to be taken into account when determining the value of the work according to \u00a7 13a Paragraph 5 No. 1 a EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "If the agreed remuneration in an employment relationship that is otherwise to be recognized under tax law does not reach the amount stipulated in the collective agreement, according to the BFH judgment of March 20, 1990 (BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "776) to apply the value of the work for the physical work pro rata according to \u00a7 13a Abs 5 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "c) If the initial value is a value share for special uses i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "of Section 13a Paragraph 4 No. 1 Sentence 2 in conjunction with"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "V with Paragraph 8 No. 1 EStG because the total of the comparative or individual income values \u200b\u200battributable to these special uses does not exceed DM 2000, no reduction by the VAK shares attributable to the special use is to be made when determining the value of the work"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "d) If, on the other hand, the value of the special uses is not included in the initial value, the physical work of the farmer and the unpaid relatives must be divided between agricultural use and special uses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "As a rule, the information provided by the taxpayer in Appendix L to the income tax return can be followed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "However, if the taxpayer has declared no or obviously incorrect proportions of the workforce (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "A rough comparison reveals that the declared division of labor by the economically necessary labor by more than 25%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "deviates), the share of the workforce attributable to the special uses must be estimated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "The estimate can be based on the labor requirement stated in Appendix 2"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "If the division of the share of the labor force between the paid workers on the one hand and the business owner and the unpaid relatives on the other hand is not easily possible, the share of the paid workers for special uses is to be determined as follows: Paid VAK x in the special branch of the business required VAK total existing VAK = proportion of the paid workforce) If temporary workers are employed whose work performance is to be taken into account when determining the maximum VAK to be applied (Section 13a (5) No. Temporary workers in VAK from the 1993/94 financial year should consider an hourly wage of 12 DM (up to the 1992/93 financial year: 10 DM) with an annual work performance of a VAK of 2100 hours (up to the 1992/93 financial year: 2400 hours)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "f) If a degree of disability has been determined due to a physical handicap of the owner or one of his employees, the value for physical work is to be set correspondingly lower (Section 13a, Paragraph 5, No. 1 a i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "V with No. 3 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Regardless of this, the value of the work performed for the management of the company (Section 13a Paragraph 5 No. 1 b EStG) is always 5 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "of the initial value"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "g) The simplification regulation of Section 130 a Paragraph 3 Sentence 7 EStR 1990 / R 130 a Paragraph 4 EStR 1993 applicable to part-time farmers does not apply if circumstances differ from the normal case (BFH judgment of 19 July 1990 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "973)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "That u can"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Seasonal work, part-time employment, deviating working time regulations, high livestock numbers or a main self-employed / commercial activity"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "There are no concerns if the value of the work in these cases with the v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "-A share is set that corresponds to the ratio of agricultural and forestry activity to the total activity of the taxpayer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "To measure the value of the work performed by part-time farmers with a farm size outside of average conditions, see ESt-Kartei (LuF) \u00a7 13a EStG No. 15h) According to \u00a7 13a Par.5 No. 4 EStG, the value of the physical work of the person in charge of the household is 20%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "to be reduced for every person fully paid and accommodated in the household"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "The people to be taken into account in the reduction also include retirees who are regularly fed in the owner's household"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "The senior citizens are also accommodated in the owner's household if the senior citizens live in an apartment based on their own right of residence, which is part of the agricultural and forestry business in terms of valuation law"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "A real security of the right of residence does not prevent this"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "i) Should taxpayers with reference to the BFH judgment of January 18, 1990 (BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "372) deviating from the lump-sum determination of the value of the work performance, request the approach of the specific labor requirement within the framework of the maximum value according to \u00a7 13a Paragraph 5 No. 6 EStG, I ask you to report to the relevant tax department"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "3 Rent income received (Section 13a (6) sentence 2 EStG) (cf. Section 130a (6) EStR 1990) If the farmer and forest manager does not declare the operating expenses attributable to the leased land, 25 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "of the comparative value applicable to the leased areas must be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "If in the lease the payment of the property tax, agricultural chamber contributions etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "has been agreed by the lessee, the agreed lease is to be taken into account without reducing operating expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "In the case of sub-leasing, the lease interest paid to the company lessor on a pro-rata basis for the sub-leased areas must be taken into account as operating expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Since the company leaseholder generally does not have to bear any additional expenses for the leased space in addition to the agreed rent, the flat-rate operating expenses cannot be granted in addition"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "The rent received also includes the income from ground rent for a property belonging to the business assets, as long as the property encumbered with the leasehold is not valued as real estate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "If the property of the business assets encumbered with the heritable building right is valued as real estate, the ground rent must be recorded in accordance with Section 13a (8) No. 3 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Income from the hunting lease for areas included in the initial value are compensated with the approach of the basic amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Income from hunting leases for areas not included in the initial value (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Forest areas) are to be taken into account as a profit correction according to \u00a7 13a Abs 8 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "For the leasing of a property with a milk quota, see ESt-Kartei (Luf) \u00a7 13 EStG No. 127 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "4 Profits according to Section 13a Paragraph 8 EStG (see Section 130 a Paragraph 8 EStR 1990 / R 130 a Paragraph 8 EStR 1993) a) The profits from special uses, which are to be recorded separately according to Section 13a Paragraph 8 No. 1 EStG, also include Profits from field vegetable cultivation (ESt-Kartei (LuF) \u00a7 13a EStG No. 21 k ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "); fruit growing (ESt-Kartei (LuF) \u00a7 13a EStG No. 22 k ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "If the income is determined on the basis of the aforementioned income tax index cards by means of an estimate, the expenses associated with the special uses for (possibly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "proportional) third party wages, rent and debt interest to be deducted from the operating income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "b) The profits from operating processes that were not taken into account when determining the initial value and are therefore to be recorded according to Section 13a (8) No. 3 EStG include, for example,"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Additional profits from sales of breeding cattle and other particularly valuable animals (ESt-Kartei (LuF) \u00a7 13a EStG No. 25 and No. 25 a); profits from the rental of rooms or apartments to holiday guests and from camping sites, as far as income from land and forestry (ESt-Kartei (LuF) \u00a7 13 EStG No. 27); interest income and dividends, as far as the capital claim or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "the security is business assets; profits from riding schools and rental of own horses, insofar as it is income from agriculture and forestry; profits from secondary employment, insofar as it is income from agriculture and forestry (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "ESt-Kartei (LuF) \u00a7 13 EStG No. 124); Profits from investments that belong to the agricultural and forestry business assets; Profits from the keeping and care of retired animals (BFH judgment of 14 April 1988 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "774); Profits from the rearing of animals in the wage system (ESt-Kartei (LuF) \u00a7 13a EStG No. 23); Profits from the rental of living space belonging to the agricultural and forestry business assets (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "from rented residential properties); profits from the sale of sugar beet allotments (ESt-Kartei (LuF) \u00a7 13 EStG Nr 132); compensation for economic difficulties (ESt-Kartei (LuF) \u00a7 13 EStG Nr 134); mast and overvoltage allowances (ESt-Kartei ( LuF) \u00a7 13 EStG No. 135); the operating processes i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 13a Paragraph 8 EStG; profits from the activity in machine and industrial aids (ESt-Kartei (LuF) \u00a7 13a EStG No. 26); remuneration for the task of milk production (ESt-Kartei (LuF) \u00a7 13 EStG No. 127 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "); Benefits from funding programs (ESt-Kartei (LuF) \u00a7 13 EStG No. 126)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "c) The processes to be recorded separately according to \u00a7 13a (8) EStG include"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Non-profit cultivation of threshing peas, French beans and head cabbage as industrial vegetables; tobacco cultivation; seed potato cultivation; keeping of father animals"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "d) Separate economic goods from the business assets, the sale or removal of which does not result in a profit correction acc"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "\u00a7 13a Abs 8 EStG would lead (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Machines, fattening animals), as a result of force majeure from the business assets and if the insurance compensation received is used for the procurement of replacement economic goods, it cannot be assumed that the acquisition / production costs of the replacement economic goods according to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Section 35 EStR 1990 / R 35 EStR 1993 have been reduced (ESt-Kartei (LuF) \u00a7 13 EStG Nr 35 Tz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Since the sale of the removed assets with the basic amount according to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "\u00a7 13a Abs 1 to 4 EStG would be settled, the profit resulting from the payment of the insurance compensation is settled with the approach of the basic amount, so that there is no need for the taxpayer to claim a tax-free profit transfer acc"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Section 35 EStR 1990 / R 35 EStR 1993 exists"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "In the event of a later transition to the determination of profits according to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "In accordance with Section 4 (1) or Section 4 (3) of the Income Tax Act, the book values \u200b\u200bof the newly acquired assets are to be calculated on the basis of the actual acquisition / production costs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "e) Profit corrections i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 13a Paragraph 8 No. 1 to 3 EStG are to be determined in principle according to \u00a7 4 Paragraph 3 EStG (BFH judgment of 29 November 1990 - BStBl 1992 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "715)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "The determination of profits by comparing the existing situation according to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Section 4 (1) of the EStG is permissible if corresponding records are actually kept"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "In this case, the taxpayer must apply this type of profit calculation to all profit corrections according to \u00a7 13a Paragraph 8 No. 1 to 3 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "A restriction to only certain parts of the profit corrections is not permitted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "All of the principles that are decisive for determining profits by comparing existing stocks, in particular recording (allocation or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Delimitation) of operational processes according to their economic affiliation to the profit determination period must be observed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "The principles of Section 4 (3) EStG must always be observed when determining the profits to be recorded in accordance with Section 13a (8) No. 4 EStG from the sale or removal of land"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "In the event of a change in the type of profit determination for the area of \u200b\u200bprofit corrections in a subsequent financial year, the principles of Section 19 EStR 1990 / R 17 EStR 1993 must be applied accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "f) The profits to be determined separately include all operating income and operating expenses (incl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "the depreciation) that are related to the respective use or the individual operating process"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "In particular, the debt interest and lease interest attributable to the correction area must be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "As far as own products, which are already recorded in the basic amount area (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "self-produced fodder) are consumed within the scope of the surcharge area, they are to be deducted there at the market price as operating expenses (BFH judgment of April 14, 1988 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "774)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Depreciation is to be taken into account for the assets that are acquired or manufactured and used for operational processes for which a profit correction according to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Section 13a (8) of the Income Tax Act is to be carried out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "g) In the determination according to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "13 EStG, the tax reduction according to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Section 34e EStG cannot be granted for profit shares that have been determined or estimated in their actual amount (BFH judgment of 28 November 1991 - BStBl 1992 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "458)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "5 Debt interest, rent paid out, permanent burdens (Section 13a (3) sentence 2 EStG) (see Section 130a (9) EStR 1990 / R 130a (6) EStR 1993) a) Debt interest"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "The principles of the decision of the Grand Senate of June 4, 1990 (BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "817) to be observed (ESt-Kartei \u00a7 4 EStG Nr 28)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "This applies in particular to interest on debt incurred on a current account, because private transactions are usually also processed via this account and a deduction may only be made as business expenses if the credit claim is due to operational purposes (BFH judgment of November 15, 1990 - BFH / NV 1991 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "805)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Interest subsidies from public funds reduce the deductible debt interest"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Regarding the income tax treatment of interest reduction subsidies according to the agricultural loan program, see ESt-Kartei (LuF) \u00a7 13 EStG No. 126b) Lease interest paid If the rent charged deviates significantly from that of the previous financial year, without the reasons (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Expansion of the leased areas) are recognizable, I ask you to clarify the matter, in particular to request the lease agreements"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Rent for farm buildings that are not in the initial value according to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Section 13a (4) of the Income Tax Act (EStG) cannot, according to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Section 13a (6) of the Income Tax Act (EStG) can be deducted because, according to this, only lease payments paid for areas with an initial value are deductible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Rent for farm buildings can, however, when determining the profit corrections i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "of Section 13a, Paragraph 8 of the Income Tax Act, insofar as they are related to such processes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Lease interest for an entire leased business is generally deductible in accordance with Section 13a (6) of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "The amount is limited to the pro-rata base amount on the basis of the total valuation attributable to the lease"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "incl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "of the surcharge according to \u00a7 41 BewG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "If the lease payment also includes the remuneration for the use of the apartment used by the lessee, the portion of the rent due to the apartment is only i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "the regulation of \u00a7 13a paragraph 7 sentence 2 EStG, if a value in use is to be assessed for the apartment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "If the lease also includes the leasing of beef cattle, which are to be returned to the leaser in the same type, quality and quantity, then a loan in kind (Sections 607 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "BGB)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "The proportional \"lease interest\" is fully deductible as debt interest according to \u00a7 13a Paragraph 3 Sentence 2 EStG (judgment of the Lower Saxony FG of 23 August 1989 - VII 35/86 - legally binding)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Correspondingly, when leasing other assets from current assets (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "standing harvest, field inventory), which is based on an agreement similar to a loan (BFH judgment of 6 December 1984 - BStBl 1985 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "391)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "On the other hand, leasing expenses for fixed assets (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Breeding cattle) only within the framework of \u00a7 13a Paragraph 3 Clause 2 i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "V with \u00a7 13a Abs 6 EStG deductible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "c) Continuous loads In the unit assessment, permanent loads that are operating expenses (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Contributions to water and soil associations, sluice and dyke loads), have always been taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "If the taxpayer asserts the deduction of permanent burdens as business expenses, then by asking the valuation office to check whether these permanent burdens have already been taken into account in the unit valuation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "For the deduction of partial retirement benefits as special expenses, see ESt-Kartei (LuF) \u00a7 13 EStG No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "14 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "If, in the reallocation process, the execution costs incurred for the production of community facilities are allocated to the members of the community of participants, the individual members acquire the right to use this facility"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "In this respect, there are acquisition or production costs that must be capitalized"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "The part of the execution costs still owed in the apportionment procedure is a liability, the repayment of which is conceptually not a permanent burden i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "of Section 13a (3) sentence 2 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "The burden on the operating result (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "through depreciation of the acquisition or production costs) is recorded with the approach of the basic amount according to \u00a7 13a Abs 4 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "6 Other additions and reductions Outside the profit corrections according to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Section 13a (8) of the Income Tax Act may include the following additions and reductions: Increased deductions for residential buildings in accordance with Section 7b of the Income Tax Act i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "V with \u00a7 52 EStDV, insofar as the value-in-use taxation is continued; profit deduction according to \u00a7 78 EStDV (see ESt-Kartei (LuF) \u00a7 13 EStG No. 136) or \u00a7 5 F\u00f6rdG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "It should be noted that the sales tax paid is not part of the preferential acquisition or manufacturing costs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "The increased deductions according to \u00a7 7b EStG are to be taken into account before the deduction amount according to \u00a7 78 EStDV (BFH judgment of 26 October 1989 - BStBl 1990 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "292)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "The tax relief according to \u00a7 78 EStDV must not lead to a loss from agriculture and forestry (\u00a7 78 Abs 3 EStDV)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Other elevated deposits (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Sections 7c, h, i and k) cannot be taken into account when determining profits in accordance with Section 13a (3) to (7) EStG because there is no corresponding legal regulation (BFH judgment of June 7, 1984 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "663)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "If the prerequisites for such special depreciation for assets that exclusively serve a part of the business whose income is to be recorded in accordance with Section 13a (8) EStG, the inclusion of the profit correction in a total profit determined in accordance with Section 13a EStG does not preclude the granting of the special depreciation (cf. to \u00a7 7d EStG ESt-Kartei (LuF) \u00a7 13a No. 12)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "7 Voluntary and tolerated business assets When determining profits according to \u00a7 13a EStG, arbitrary business assets cannot be formed (BFH judgment of 23 May 1991 - BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "798)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "If the use of assets that are permissibly assigned to business assets (in particular assets of the necessary business assets) changes and these are not to be assigned to the necessary private assets due to the change in use, the assets remain in the business assets until they are clearly removed (Section 4 Para 1 sentence 4 EStG, section 13 a paragraph 3 sentence 4 EStR 1990 / R 14 paragraph 3 sentence 6 EStR 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "8 Lease in the current financial year If the business is leased in the course of the financial year without a declaration of abandonment, the profit for this financial year is to be considered as a uniform financial year profit (no two short financial years) in accordance with"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "To determine \u00a7 13a EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "The determination of the profit takes place in such a way that the basic amount (\u00a7 13a Abs 4 EStG), the valuation for the work performance (\u00a7 13a Abs 5 EStG) incl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "of the valuation for the management of the business (Section 13a (5) No. 5 EStG) must be taken into account on a pro-rata basis"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "The other income and expenses incurred in the financial year - in particular lease income (incl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "the rent received from the company lease), lease expenses (if applicable"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Pay attention to the proportionate distribution in the case of limitation by the proportionate base amount), debt interest and profit corrections in accordance with"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Section 13a (8) EStG - are taken into account in full"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "The annual profit determined in this way is to be divided over the assessment periods according to the general principles"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "9 Profit distribution in a partnership that determines the profit from agriculture and forestry according to \u00a7 13a EStG If the profit of an agricultural and forestry operation, which is run in the legal form of a partnership, is determined permissible according to \u00a7 13a EStG, then the profit distribution is basically according to to carry out the corporate law agreements made, if the distribution is intended solely on a per capita basis or according to a percentage ratio"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "If, according to the articles of association, shares in the profit are to be allocated to the shareholders in advance (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "for the activity in the company, for the interest on the capital employed), the profit determined according to \u00a7 13a EStG is to be divided according to the ratio that results from the distribution of the profit actually generated and distributed to the shareholders"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "10 Estimate of the tax bases acc"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Section 162 AO If the tax bases of a farmer and forest manager authorized to determine profits according to Section 13a of the Income Tax Act are to be estimated due to failure to submit tax returns according to Section 162 AO, it is not permissible to use the average rate profit freely or on the basis of the standard rates for businesses that are subject to accounting (cf. Card index (LuF) \u00a7 13 EStG No. 42 k ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "No. 43 k ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": ") appreciate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "In these cases, an average rate profit calculation is to be carried out, in which only individual tax bases that are not evident from the tax files (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "The size of the leasehold areas, the value of the work performed, the amount of debt interest, the extent of the necessary profit adjustments) are to be estimated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Text of Annex 1: Maximum permitted number of animals in livestock units (VE) according to Section 13a Paragraph 1 No. 3 EStG and Section 13 Paragraph 1 No. 1 EStG (see Section I No. 2) Maximum number of animals permitted in VE when the requirements according to Section 13a Paragraph 1 No. 3 are checked EStG with a share in the animal herds Regularly agriculturally used areas in habis to 75%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Pigs and poultry over 75 BC"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107786.xml"}, "text": "Pigs and Gefl\u00fcgelbei the breakdown by \u00a7 13 1 # 1 \u00fcr any other ha3315Text Appendix 2: economically necessary in fruit and vegetable Arbeitskr\u00e4fteVAK / ha1Obstbaua) core and Steinobst025b) Beerenobst025aa) Erdbeeren065bb) Johannisbeeren0602Weinbau123Spargelbau0404Gr\u00fcne peas (canned peas) a) Pfl\u00fcckerbsen02